The Nautilus DevOps team is conducting application deployment tests on selected application servers. They require a nginx container deployment on Application Server 1. 
Complete the task with the following instructions:
On Application Server 1 create a container named nginx_1 using the nginx image with the alpine tag. Ensure container is in a running state.

solutions:-
Step-by-Step Instructions
SSH into Application Server 1 If you're not already on the server:

ssh user@application-server-1
Pull the Nginx Alpine Image This ensures the latest lightweight version is available:

docker pull nginx:alpine
Run the Container Create and start the container named nginx_1:

docker run -d --name nginx_1 nginx:alpine
-d runs the container in detached mode.

--name nginx_1 assigns the container name.

nginx:alpine specifies the image and tag.

Verify the Container is Running Check its status:


docker ps -f name=nginx_1
You should see output showing the container is Up.

âœ… Quick Validation
If you want to test Nginx is serving content:


docker exec nginx_1 wget -qO- localh
